        "id": 9053,
        "name": "John Brownlee",
        "username": "john_brownlee",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/john_brownlee/{size}/22_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-02-08T23:24:27.972Z",
        "cooked": "<p>In general for multi-DC configurations, I would recommend using 9 coordinators, with no more than 3 in any DC. For your configuration that would mean 3 in each DC. That ensures that you can lose an entire region, and even one machine in a second region, without losing a majority of your coordinators.</p>\n<p>In the configuration you specified, transaction durability is only local in the primary DC, and DC_C is not going to be serving any roles besides having coordinators. That could allow you to fail over manually, with data loss, in the event that you lose DC_A, but you wouldn\u2019t be able to automatically fail over.</p>",
